div.p:
Next, as for the marompuni name of Ompu Tuvan Binur hata ni aji, a great wandering Datu [of] every part of the whole worlds, who takes care of the gold, the yellow one, [whose] hands are white-spotted;
[whose] fingers are rurus (dropping? slender?); since the coins are in the great lobuan, I am the invisible bride-price, from the area of Palipi, of the marga Sinaga, Grandfather Ratus (Hundred)
who has never lost any magic war relying on the great Pangulubalang Duva Raja Ojim, relying on the great (magical preparation) Panuruni Balagori, relying on (the aggressive magic of) the Pabuhu Tanduk Si anggasana Si manoktohi;
who cannot be sent back home by the male, [for instance] a  datu; who cannot be sent away by the woman [for instance] a great Si Baso.
